<div><div><h2>ONGC second-quarter profit rises, beats estimate</h2></div><div>new delhi (reuters) - india s oil and natural gas corp ltd posted a 61 percent jump in second-quarter profit on saturday with higher crude oil prices helping it to beat forecasts. ongc s net profit stood at 82.65 billion rupees ($1.14 billion) in the quarter ended sept. 30 compared with 51.3 billion rupees a year earlier the company said in a stock exchange filing. analysts on average had expected a profit of 68.61 billion rupees according to refinitiv data. income from operations rose by 47.5 percent to 279.89 billion rupees ongc said. ($1 = 72.4350 indian rupees) all quotes delayed a minimum of 15 minutes. see here for a complete list of exchanges and delays.   2018 reuters. all rights reserved.</div></div>